_Pa’al_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_pa’al_ future tense]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|| *Singular* |\<| *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | אֶכְתֹּב <br><br> _echtoiv_ <br><br><br> I will write | \< | נִכְתֹּב <br><br> _nichtoiv_ <br><br><br> We will write | \< |
| *Second-Person* | תִּכְתֹּב <br><br> _tichtov_ <br><br><br> You [male] will write | תִּכְתְּבִי <br><br> _tichtevi_ <br><br><br> You [female] will write  | תִּכְתְּבוּ <br><br> _tichtevu_ <br><br><br> You [males] will write  | תִּכְתֹּבְנָה <br><br> _tichtoivnau_ <br><br><br> You [females] will write  |
| *Third-Person* | יִכְתֹּב <br><br> _yichtoiv_ <br><br><br> He will write | תִּכְתֹּב <br><br> _tichtov_ <br><br><br> She will write  | יִכְתְּבוּ <br><br> _yichtevu_ <br><br><br> [Those males] will write  | תִּכְתֹּבְנָה <br><br> _tichtoivnau_ <br><br><br> [Those females] will write  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎כ, ‎ת, and ב above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
